    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>GPIO pull strength flags</header>
      <description><para>The pull strength flags are a Zephyr specific extension of the standard GPIO flags specified by the Linux GPIO binding.</para>
<para>Only applicable for NXP IMX SoCs.</para>
<para>The interface supports two different pull strengths: <computeroutput>WEAK</computeroutput> - The lowest pull strength supported by the HW <computeroutput>STRONG</computeroutput> - The highest pull strength supported by the HW </para>
</description>
